Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> How can we make Hush more accessible to people without stable internet access?

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <dukeleto> not an easy thing, but worth thinking about. I want to support all use cases we can. It's possible to store a transaction in a QR code, and receive it off-line, then verify it later when you have internet, and submit to the network. There are some ways to do things without internet, but we have no GUIs or documentation about it.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <Crypto99> We can make Hush more accessible to those without stable internet access in a few ways.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <Crypto99> The issue is, even if they could get it, how would they use it?

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <Crypto99> One, sending it by phone number.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <Crypto99> Two, incentivizing people to run internet relays and create a mesh network.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <Crypto99> Three, make small  $25 beeper like messaging devices, to use HushMessenger

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrd-hush] <Crypto99> A bitcoin atm operates to where it can shoot out a paper, with a private & public address with a QR Code. Then you load money & it goes to the address and you import it later
